gomodel:SYNGO_2322  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunoparticles for Netrin-G1 were mostly detected in the presynaptic active zone membrane of dendritic spines in SR.\n\n2/1/2018 Pim\n- Literal: \"Excitatory asymmetric synapses immunolabeled with netrin-G1 and netrin-G2 antibodies were detected in the SLM and SR, respectively (Fig. 1D)\"....\"Netrin-G1 and netrin-G2 immunoparticles had peak radial distances within the first external bin from the presynaptic membrane (i.e., within the synaptic cleft)\" ... \"These findings indicate that netrin-Gs are presynaptic proteins and NGLs are postsynaptic proteins.\" Note: 'SR' means 'CA1 stratum radiatum'\n- Based on the known lipid anchor of the protein, the \"anchored component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nElectron microscopy\nFor post-embedding iEM, adult mice were deeply anesthetized." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099029 replaced by GO:0048787" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2322" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

